We calculated a SARI etiologic fraction (SEF) (also known as population attributable fraction) for each pathogen for which incidence was measured (above) [40,41]. For this analysis, SEF ﻿is the proportion of SARI cases that might theoretically be eliminated if the etiology were eliminated (assuming a primary role for that etiologic pathogen in causing pneumonia). SEF is given as:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
